{"body":"## Problem

`sequant init --mcp` detects Claude Desktop, Cursor, and VS Code + Continue — but **not Claude Code**, which is the tool sequant users are actually running inside. The MCP setup is behind a `--mcp` flag and only writes to global client config files, missing the primary integration point entirely.

Claude Code reads MCP server configs from `.mcp.json` in the project root. This file doesn't get created by `sequant init` at all today.

### Current behavior

```
sequant init          → no MCP setup
sequant init --mcp    → writes to ~/Library/.../claude_desktop_config.json, Cursor, VS Code
sequant init --yes    → no MCP setup (--mcp not implied)
```

Claude Code users get nothing unless they manually create `.mcp.json`.

### Why this matters

- Claude Code is the primary runtime for sequant — every sequant user runs inside it
- `.mcp.json` is project-scoped and version-controlled — team members get it automatically
- Global client configs (Claude Desktop, Cursor) are secondary and require modifying user-level files

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] **AC-1:** `sequant init` creates `.mcp.json` in the project root with the sequant MCP server config by default (no `--mcp` flag required)
- [ ] **AC-2:** `.mcp.json` appears in the "Will create:" preview during init
- [ ] **AC-3:** If `.mcp.json` already exists with a `sequant` entry, skip creation (don't duplicate)
- [ ] **AC-4:** If `.mcp.json` already exists without a `sequant` entry, merge it in (preserve existing servers)
- [ ] **AC-5:** `--mcp` flag retains its current behavior of ALSO writing to global client configs (Claude Desktop, Cursor, VS Code)
- [ ] **AC-6:** `sequant init --yes` creates `.mcp.json` (always) but skips global client config changes (no global file modifications in non-interactive mode, consistent with current --yes behavior for --mcp)
- [ ] **AC-7:** Existing tests pass; add test coverage for `.mcp.json` creation and merge logic

## Design

### `.mcp.json` format

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "sequant": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["sequant@latest", "serve"]
    }
  }
}
```

Note: no `cwd` needed — Claude Code runs from the project root where `.mcp.json` lives.

### Init flow (proposed)

```
sequant init
├── Creates .sequant/, .claude/, scripts/dev/ (existing)
├── Creates .mcp.json with sequant server config   ← NEW (always)
└── Interactive: "Also add to Claude Desktop/Cursor?" (only with --mcp or interactive prompt)

sequant init --yes
├── Creates everything above including .mcp.json   ← NEW
└── Skips global client detection (no --mcp implied)

sequant init --mcp
├── Creates .mcp.json
└── ALSO writes to detected global client configs (existing behavior)
```

### Merge logic for existing `.mcp.json`

```typescript
// Pseudocode
if (!exists('.mcp.json')) {
  write('.mcp.json', { mcpServers: { sequant: config } });
} else {
  const existing = JSON.parse(read('.mcp.json'));
  if (existing.mcpServers?.sequant) {
    // Already configured — skip
  } else {
    existing.mcpServers = { ...existing.mcpServers, sequant: config };
    write('.mcp.json', existing);
  }
}
```

## Files in Scope

- `src/commands/init.ts` — main init logic
- `src/lib/mcp-config.ts` — MCP config detection and generation

## Out of Scope

- Removing the `--mcp` flag (it still has value for global client configs)
- Adding `.mcp.json` to `.gitignore` (it should be committed for team portability)","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOQzPeLM8AAAACT-M2TQ","name":"enhancement","description":"New feature or request","color":"a2eeef"},{"id":"LA_kwDOQzPeLM8AAAACUl1BaQ","name":"planned","description":"Implementation plan approved","color":"0E8A16"},{"id":"LA_kwDOQzPeLM8AAAACVOX0xg","name":"cli","description":"CLI commands and interface","color":"5319E7"}],"state":"OPEN","title":"sequant init: create .mcp.json by default for Claude Code MCP integration"}

